Mplus VERSION 8.10 (Mac)
MUTHEN & MUTHEN
06/24/2026  11:45 AM

INPUT INSTRUCTIONS

  TITLE:
    Didactic RSA example for the franzpak MODEL CONSTRAINT vignette.
    Two latent predictors (X, Y) and their polynomial/interaction terms predict
    two latent outcomes (Z1, Z2). The response-surface (RSA) parameters a1-a5 are
    defined per outcome in MODEL CONSTRAINT as NEW(...) parameters.
    Generic indicator names (x1-x4, y1-y4, z11-z16, z21-z26) keep the example
    self-contained.

  DATA:
    FILE = "rsa_constraints.dat";

  VARIABLE:
    NAMES =
      x1 x2 x3 x4
      y1 y2 y3 y4
      z11 z12 z13 z14 z15 z16
      z21 z22 z23 z24 z25 z26;

    USEVARIABLES =
      x1 x2 x3 x4
      y1 y2 y3 y4
      z11 z12 z13 z14 z15 z16
      z21 z22 z23 z24 z25 z26;

    MISSING = .;

  ANALYSIS:
    TYPE = RANDOM;
    ESTIMATOR = BAYES;
    PROCESSORS = 4;

  MODEL:
    ! --- Measurement models ---
    X  BY x1 x2 x3 x4;            ! predictor X
    Y  BY y1 y2 y3 y4;           ! predictor Y
    Z1 BY z11 z12 z13 z14 z15 z16;  ! outcome 1
    Z2 BY z21 z22 z23 z24 z25 z26;  ! outcome 2

    ! --- Polynomial / interaction terms (latent moderation via XWITH) ---
    XY | X XWITH Y;   ! interaction
    XS | X XWITH X;   ! X squared
    YS | Y XWITH Y;   ! Y squared

    ! --- Regression on outcome 1 (Z1) ---
    Z1 ON X  (b1)
          Y  (b2)
          XS (b3)
          XY (b4)
          YS (b5);

    ! --- Regression on outcome 2 (Z2) ---
    Z2 ON X  (bb1)
          Y  (bb2)
          XS (bb3)
          XY (bb4)
          YS (bb5);

  MODEL CONSTRAINT:
    NEW(cs_1 cc_1 is_1 ic_1 a5_1
        cs_2 cc_2 is_2 ic_2 a5_2);

    ! RSA surface parameters - outcome Z1
    cs_1 = b1 + b2;          ! a1: slope along line of congruence (LOC)
    cc_1 = b3 + b4 + b5;     ! a2: curvature along LOC
    is_1 = b1 - b2;          ! a3: slope along line of incongruence (LOIC)
    ic_1 = b3 - b4 + b5;     ! a4: curvature along LOIC
    a5_1 = b3 - b5;          ! a5: FPA = LOC test (Nestler et al.)

    ! RSA surface parameters - outcome Z2
    cs_2 = bb1 + bb2;        ! a1: slope along line of congruence (LOC)
    cc_2 = bb3 + bb4 + bb5;  ! a2: curvature along LOC
    is_2 = bb1 - bb2;        ! a3: slope along line of incongruence (LOIC)
    ic_2 = bb3 - bb4 + bb5;  ! a4: curvature along LOIC
    a5_2 = bb3 - bb5;        ! a5: FPA = LOC test (Nestler et al.)

  OUTPUT:
    STDYX CINTERVAL TECH1;



INPUT READING TERMINATED NORMALLY




Didactic RSA example for the franzpak MODEL CONSTRAINT vignette.
Two latent predictors (X, Y) and their polynomial/interaction terms predict
two latent outcomes (Z1, Z2). The response-surface (RSA) parameters a1-a5 are
defined per outcome in MODEL CONSTRAINT as NEW(...) parameters.
Generic indicator names (x1-x4, y1-y4, z11-z16, z21-z26) keep the example
self-contained.

